---
title: "REQFIT Pipeline — 5-Phase LangGraph Sequence"
---
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant UI as React UI
    participant API as FastAPI :8000
    participant Q as Redis (Queue)
    participant W as Celery Worker
    participant PG as PostgreSQL
    participant QD as Qdrant
    participant LLM as Claude API

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Upload & Dispatch ━━━

    UI->>API: POST /upload (file)
    API->>PG: INSERT uploads (metadata, hash)
    API-->>UI: 201 {upload_id}

    UI->>API: POST /run {upload_id, config}
    API->>PG: INSERT batches (status=pending)
    API->>Q: Celery task dispatch
    API-->>UI: 202 {batch_id, ws_url}

    UI->>API: WS /ws/progress/{batch_id}
    API->>Q: SUBSCRIBE progress:{batch_id}

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Phase 1 — Ingestion ━━━

    W->>Q: PhaseStartEvent(phase=1)
    Q-->>API: forward
    API-->>UI: phase_start

    W->>W: G1-lite: validate file (magic bytes, size, hash)
    W->>W: Docling: parse PDF/DOCX → tables + prose
    W->>W: Header mapping (synonym YAML)
    W->>W: G3-lite: injection scan (10 regex)
    W->>W: G2: PII redaction (Presidio + spaCy)
    W->>LLM: Atomize + classify intent + tag module
    LLM-->>W: atoms[]
    W->>W: Deduplicate (cosine > 0.92 merge)
    W->>W: Quality gates (ambiguity, completeness, schema)

    W->>Q: PhaseCompleteEvent(validated_atoms, flagged_atoms)
    Q-->>API: forward
    API-->>UI: phase_complete

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over W,Q: Gate 1→2: reject if zero validated atoms
    end

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Phase 2 — Knowledge Retrieval (RAG) ━━━

    W->>Q: PhaseStartEvent(phase=2)

    par Source A: Capabilities
        W->>QD: Hybrid search (dense + BM25 + RRF)
        QD-->>W: top-20 capabilities
    and Source B: MS Learn
        W->>QD: Dense search (docs collection)
        QD-->>W: top-10 doc chunks
    and Source C: Historical Fitments
        W->>PG: pgvector query (module filter)
        PG-->>W: 0–5 prior fitments
    end

    W->>W: RRF fusion (A=primary, B=boost, C=structured)
    W->>W: Cross-encoder rerank (ms-marco-MiniLM)
    W->>W: Adaptive-K cutoff + confidence calibration

    W->>Q: PhaseCompleteEvent(retrieval_contexts[])

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over W,Q: Gate 2→3: reject if retrieval failure
    end

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Phase 3 — Semantic Matching ━━━

    W->>Q: PhaseStartEvent(phase=3)

    W->>W: Compute 5 signals per (atom, capability)
    Note right of W: cosine(0.25) + entity(0.20)<br/>+ token(0.15) + history(0.25)<br/>+ rerank(0.15)
    W->>W: Anomaly detection (cosine↑ but entity↓)
    W->>W: Route assignment per atom

    W->>Q: PhaseCompleteEvent(match_results[] + routes)

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over W,Q: Gate 3→4: continue with routes
    end

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Phase 4 — Classification (LLM Reasoning) ━━━

    W->>Q: PhaseStartEvent(phase=4)

    alt FAST_TRACK (score > 0.85 + history)
        W->>LLM: 1 call (top-1 cap + priors)
        LLM-->>W: ClassificationResult
    else DEEP_REASON (0.60 ≤ score ≤ 0.85)
        par 3 independent calls
            W->>LLM: Call 1 (compatibility consultant)
            W->>LLM: Call 2 (strict engineer)
            W->>LLM: Call 3 (gap analyst)
        end
        LLM-->>W: 3 results → majority vote
    else GAP_CONFIRM (score < 0.60)
        W->>LLM: 1 call (confirm gap + effort)
        LLM-->>W: ClassificationResult(GAP)
    end

    W->>W: G8: Prompt firewall (Jinja2 autoescape)
    W->>W: G9: Output schema enforcer (Pydantic v2)
    W->>W: G11: Response PII scanner

    loop Per atom classified
        W->>Q: ClassificationEvent(atom_id, result)
        Q-->>API: forward
        API-->>UI: classification (live streaming)
    end

    W->>Q: PhaseCompleteEvent(classifications[])

    rect rgb(255, 230, 230)
        Note over W,Q: Gate 4→5: continue to validation
    end

    Note over UI,LLM: ━━━ Phase 5 — Validation + HITL ━━━

    W->>Q: PhaseStartEvent(phase=5)
    W->>W: G10-lite: sanity gate (contradiction flags)

    alt Flagged items exist
        W->>PG: Checkpoint state (LangGraph interrupt)
        W->>Q: ReviewRequiredEvent(flagged_count, reasons)
        Q-->>API: forward
        API-->>UI: review_required

        Note over UI,API: ── Human Review Loop ──
        UI->>API: GET /review (queue)
        API-->>UI: flagged items + evidence

        loop Per flagged item
            UI->>API: POST /review/{atom_id} (decision)
            API->>PG: INSERT review_items
        end

        API->>Q: Resume Celery task
        W->>PG: Load checkpoint, merge overrides
    end

    W->>W: Restore PII (pii_redaction_map)
    W->>PG: INSERT batch_results (all atoms)
    W->>PG: INSERT fitments (Source C for future waves)
    W->>W: Generate Excel report

    W->>Q: CompleteEvent(summary, report_url)
    Q-->>API: forward
    API-->>UI: complete

    UI->>API: GET /report
    API-->>UI: Excel download
